//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_image_rekon}

NOTE: This operation lists all tags for a
{rbtga_vessel}
package in
{rbtgi_repository}
using the Docker Registry HTTP API V2.
Raw tag enumeration — no hallmark parsing or health classification.

The
{rbtr_director}
rekons image tags:

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbtga_vessel}
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_MONIKER»` provided as first argument (vessel moniker)
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if missing: "Vessel moniker parameter required"

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Construct Registry Endpoint*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«REGISTRY_HOST»` as `{rbrr_gcp_region}-docker.pkg.dev`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«TAG_LIST_URL»` as `«REGISTRY_HOST»/v2/{rbrr_depot_project_id}/{rbrr_gar_repository}/«INPUT_MONIKER»/tags/list`

//axhos_step
. *Fetch Tag List*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://github.com/opencontainers/distribution-spec/blob/main/spec.md#listing-tags[Docker Registry API: tag list] with:
... method: `GET`
... endpoint: `«TAG_LIST_URL»`
... header: `Authorization: Bearer «DIRECTOR_TOKEN»`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response with JSON body containing `tags` array
.. {rbbc_store}
`«TAGS»` as array of tag strings
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if request fails: "Tag list failed with HTTP «STATUS_CODE»"

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbst_locator}
. *Display Results*:
.. {rbbc_show}
vessel moniker and tag count
.. For each tag in `«TAGS»`:
... {rbbc_show}
tag name

//axhoc_completion
Procedure completes successfully when all tags for the vessel have been listed.

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_image_delete}

NOTE: This operation jettisons a container image from
{rbtgi_repository}
using the Docker Registry HTTP API V2 implemented by
{gar_service}.

NOTE: To delete an entire {rbtga_ark} (the full `hallmarks/«HALLMARK»/` subtree — every basename including `image`, `about`, `vouch`, and any `pouch`/`diags`/`attest` tags present), use {rbtgo_ark_abjure} instead.

The
{rbtr_director}
jettisons an image by {rbst_locator}:

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbst_locator}
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_LOCATOR»` provided as first argument in `moniker:tag` format
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if missing: "Locator parameter required (moniker:tag)"
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if malformed (no colon): "Invalid locator format. Expected moniker:tag"
.. {rbbc_store}
`«MONIKER»` as portion before first colon
.. {rbbc_store}
`«TAG»` as portion after first colon

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Confirm Jettison*:
.. Unless `--force` flag is provided:
... {rbbc_show}
`Will jettison: «INPUT_LOCATOR»`
... {rbbc_require}
user types `yes` to confirm
... {rbbc_fatal}
if not confirmed: "prompt not confirmed."

//axhos_step
. *Jettison Tag*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://github.com/opencontainers/distribution-spec/blob/main/spec.md#deleting-tags[Docker Registry API: DELETE manifests] with:
... method: `DELETE`
... endpoint: `«REGISTRY_BASE»/«MONIKER»/manifests/«TAG»`
... header: `Authorization: Bearer «DIRECTOR_TOKEN»`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 202 (Accepted) or 204 (No Content) response
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if jettison fails: "Jettison failed with HTTP «STATUS_CODE»"

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbst_locator}
. *Display Results*:
.. {rbbc_show}
`Jettisoned or nonexistent: «INPUT_LOCATOR»`

//axhoc_completion
Procedure completes successfully when the tag has been jettisoned from the registry and the jettisoned message is displayed.

