== {rbtr_director} Operations

[[rbtgo_trigger_build]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_trigger_build}

ELIMINATED (₣Av): Trigger dispatch replaced by direct `builds.create` API submission.
Build context delivered via {rbtga_ark_pouch} (FROM SCRATCH OCI image in GAR).
Hallmark minted on the host before submission, passed to Cloud Build via `_RBGY_HALLMARK` substitution variable.

// include::RBSTB-trigger_build.adoc[]

NOTE: For multi-platform build authentication challenges and research findings, see link:RBWMBX-BuildxMultiPlatformAuth.adoc[RBWMBX: Buildx Multi-Platform Authentication Memo].

[[rbtgo_depot_inscribe]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_depot_inscribe}

Inscribes a reliquary into the
{rbtgi_depot}:
mirrors upstream tool images into a datestamped GAR namespace
({rbtgog_depot}).

include::RBSDI-depot_inscribe.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_director_yoke]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_director_yoke}

Yokes a reliquary stamp into a conjure vessel's
{rbrv_regime}:
validates the stamp against GAR and the vessel against its enrollment, then rewrites `RBRV_RELIQUARY` in the vessel's `rbrv.env`
({rbtgog_depot}).

include::RBSDY-director_yoke.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_image_delete]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_image_delete}

Jettisons
{rbtgi_image}
artifacts
({rbtgog_image}).

include::RBSIJ-image_jettison.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_image_retrieve]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_image_retrieve}

Wrests
{rbtgi_image}
artifacts
({rbtgog_image}).

include::RBSIW-image_wrest.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_image_rekon]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_image_rekon}

Lists all tags for a
{rbtga_vessel}
package in
{rbtgi_repository}
({rbtgog_image}).

include::RBSIR-image_rekon.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_ark_abjure]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_ark_abjure}

Formally renounces an
{rbtga_ark}
from the repository
({rbtgog_ark}),
removing its image, about, and vouch artifacts as a coherent unit.

include::RBSAA-ark_abjure.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_ark_ordain]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_ark_ordain}

Ordains a hallmark from a vessel — the master ceremony dispatch operation.
Detects vessel mode (conjure, bind, or graft) and delegates to the appropriate
{rbtga_ark}
creation path, then chains metadata and vouch pipeline stages.

[[rbtgo_ark_conjure]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_ark_conjure}

Conjures an
{rbtga_ark_image}
by building a container image
({rbtgog_ark})
from a vessel specification.
Build context delivered via {rbtga_ark_pouch}, submitted via `builds.create` API. The combined job produces both the `image` and `about` packages under the hallmark subtree (about steps embedded via stitch). Vouch is a separate Cloud Build job using DSSE envelope signature verification.

include::RBSAC-ark_conjure.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_ark_enshrine]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_ark_enshrine}

Enshrines upstream base images into
{gar_service}
({rbtgog_ark}),
producing content-addressed
{rbrv_image_anchor}
references from
{rbrv_image_origin}
declarations.
The
{rbtr_director}
submits a Cloud Build job that copies each upstream image by tag to GAR with a human-readable anchor tag, and writes the anchor back to the vessel regime.

include::RBSAE-ark_enshrine.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_ark_graft]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_ark_graft}

Grafts a locally-built container image into the
{rbtgi_repository}
({rbtgog_ark})
via native docker/podman push.
The image push itself is local (no Cloud Build); about and vouch follow as Cloud Build jobs.

include::RBSAG-ark_graft.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_ark_about]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_ark_about}

Assembles the
{rbtga_ark_about}
metadata artifact for an existing
{rbtga_ark_image}
({rbtgog_ark}).
Runs Syft for SBOM generation and builds mode-aware `build_info.json` using uniform
{gcb_service}
steps.
Conjure and bind embed these steps in their primary Cloud Build job alongside image production; graft's primary job consists of these steps alone.

include::RBSAB-ark_about.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_ark_vouch]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_ark_vouch}

Vouches for an
{rbtga_ark}
({rbtgog_ark}),
producing a
{rbtga_ark_vouch}
that records mode-aware verification results.
Conjure: DSSE envelope signature verification (Python 3 + openssl against GCB attestor keys).
Bind: digest-pin comparison.
Graft: GRAFTED stamp.
Submitted as a
{gcb_service}
job via `builds.create` after
{rbtgo_ark_about}
completes.

include::RBSAV-ark_vouch.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_director_vouch]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_director_vouch}

Batch-vouches every pending
{rbtga_ark}
hallmark in
{rbtgi_repository}
({rbtgog_ark}).
Dispatches {rbtgo_ark_vouch} per pending hallmark; mode-specific verification (conjure, bind, graft) happens inside that operation, not in the batch.
Any vouch failure terminates the batch fail-fast at the broken hallmark.

include::RBSDV-director_vouch.adoc[]

== {rbtr_retriever} Operations

[[rbtgo_hallmark_tally]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_hallmark_tally}

Enumerates every
{rbtga_ark}
hallmark in
{rbtgi_repository}
({rbtgog_ark}),
classifying each by artifact completeness and vouch status.

include::RBSCL-consecration_tally.adoc[]

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_ark_abjure}

NOTE: This operation formally renounces an
{rbtga_ark}
from
{rbtgi_repository}
by enumerating and deleting every package beneath the ark's
hallmark subtree via the GAR REST API implemented by
{gar_service}.

An
{rbtga_ark}
is the coherent unit of a Recipe Bottle build: a set of packages rooted at
`hallmarks/«HALLMARK»/` and distinguished by basename.
The
{rbtga_ark_image}
(basename `image`) contains the container image itself.
The
{rbtga_ark_about}
(basename `about`) contains SBOM and build metadata.
The
{rbtga_ark_vouch}
(basename `vouch`) contains verification results.
The
{rbtga_ark_pouch}
(basename `pouch`) contains the build context (conjure/bind only, absent for graft).
A fifth basename, `diags`, is present for conjure arks only (build-time diagnostics forwarded to the about pipeline).
For conjure vessels, a single `attest` package holds per-platform tags (`attest:«HALLMARK»-«ARCH»`).
Abjuring an ark deletes every package discovered beneath the hallmark subtree as a single logical operation.

The
{rbtr_director}
abjures an ark:

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbtga_ark}
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_VESSEL»` provided as first argument (retained for AAK signature compatibility; not used to construct the subtree path, drops in AAL)
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_HALLMARK»` provided as second argument
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if hallmark missing: "Hallmark parameter required"

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbtga_hallmark}
. *Validate Hallmark Format*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_HALLMARK»` matches pattern `[cbg]\d{12}-r\d{12}` (mode prefix + dual timestamp)
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if malformed: "Hallmark format invalid"

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Construct Hallmark Subtree*:
.. {rbbc_store}
